# TypeScript Conventions

- Use explicit types for exported functions, constants, and public interfaces.
- Keep modules focused: one primary responsibility per file.
- Prefer small pure helper functions for scoring, timing, and question validation logic.
- Avoid `any`; use union types or narrow interfaces when possible.
- Reuse existing domain types before adding new duplicated shapes.
- Keep browser/game-state side effects in dedicated services or managers.
- For gameplay changes, keep data files (`questions`, `banks`) separate from runtime logic.
